   shortterm, short-term, medium-term and long-term time horizons. Data
   collected from a 30-MW wind farm on the west coast of Nouakchott
   (Mauritania) were used in the computational analysis. In comparison to
   nonparametric models from the literature and models employing artificial
   intelligence machine learning techniques, the proposed ANFIS-MoW model
   demonstrated superior predictions for the output power of the WT with
   the fusion of very few data collected from different WTs. Moreover, for
   various time series windows (TSW) and meteorological conditions,
