   best classifier to predict the operating mode of HSCPP with an accuracy
   of similar to 2\% compared to NB and J48. Under the studied conditions
   the Regression analysis using REPTree was found to outperform SMOreg and
   achieved a relative absolute error similar to 20 kWh. The productivity
   of the HSCPP is highly affected by maximum air temperature
   (T-air,T-Max), the average temperature of air (T (air,Avg)), solar
   irradiation standard deviation (SolarRad(STD)), and maximum wind speed
   (W-sp,W-Max). Under optimal conditions, the HSCPP generates an
